The paper also discusses attack models and their corresponding defenses, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also mentions the use of deep-learning models, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence, hence cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of CIFAR10 and MNIST datasets, which are commonly used in computer vision, hence cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of distributed learning, which is a subfield of distributed computing, hence cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also a possible sub-category.
